## Configuration: `agent_config.yml`

`agent_config.yml` is the single source of truth for dynamic parts of the project. Edit it to add or remove retrievers and tools — the generator produces the corresponding DAB resource files and code stubs automatically.

```yaml
retrievers:
  - name: docs
    data_source_url: https://docs.databricks.com/en/doc-sitemap.xml
    vs_endpoint: {{ vector_search_endpoint }}
    vs_index: {{ project_name }}_docs_index
    description: "Retrieves Databricks documentation"
  # Add more retrievers here — each gets its own data prep + vector search job

tools:
  - name: execute_python_code
    signature: "code: str"
    return_type: "str"
  - name: summarize
    signature: "text: str, max_words: int"
    return_type: "str"
  # Add more tools here — each gets a stub in tools/agent_tools/
```

### Adding a retriever

1. Append a new entry to `retrievers:` in `agent_config.yml`
2. Run `make generate` — creates the data prep + vector search jobs in `retriever/resources/generated/`
3. Run `make deploy TARGET=dev` to deploy and run the new pipeline

### Adding a tool

1. Append a new entry to `tools:` in `agent_config.yml`
2. Run `make generate` — creates a stub in `tools/agent_tools/<name>.py` with a `TODO` marker
3. Implement the function in the generated stub
4. Run `make deploy TARGET=dev` for the tools bundle

