## Deploy

### Prerequisites

- Databricks CLI v0.238.0+: `pip install databricks-cli` or `brew install databricks/tap/databricks`
- Authenticated: `databricks configure` or set `DATABRICKS_HOST` + `DATABRICKS_TOKEN`

### First-time setup

```bash
# 1. Generate DAB resource files from agent_config.yml
make generate

# 2. Deploy and run each bundle in order
{%- if include_retriever == "yes" %}
make deploy-retriever TARGET=dev
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_tools == "yes" %}
make deploy-tools TARGET=dev
{%- endif %}
{%- if include_agent == "yes" %}
make deploy-agent TARGET=dev
{%- endif %}
```

Or deploy everything at once:

```bash
make deploy-all TARGET=dev
```

### Targets

| Target | Purpose |
|--------|---------|
| `dev` | Default. Individual development. |
| `staging` | Pre-production validation. CI deploys here on PR. |
| `prod` | Production. CI deploys here on merge to main. |

### Overriding variables without editing YAML

```bash
# Via CLI flag
databricks bundle deploy -t dev --var="uc_catalog=my_catalog" --var="schema=my_schema"

# Via environment variables
BUNDLE_VAR_uc_catalog=my_catalog BUNDLE_VAR_schema=my_schema databricks bundle deploy -t dev
```

Use the same overrides when deploying each bundle so they all share the same catalog and schema.

